description: This table contains information about a patient's med dispense history from a third-party interface. This information can be helpful for reviewing whether a patient is getting their prescriptions filled at the correct intervals.

columns.name: DOCUMENT_ID
columns.description: This item stores the Received Document record ID.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE_REAL
columns.description: A unique contact date in decimal format. The integer portion of the number indicates the date of contact. The digits after the decimal distinguish different contacts on the same date and are unique for each contact on that date. For example, .00 is the first/only contact, .01 is the second contact, etc.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this contact. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this contact.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE
columns.description: The date of this contact in calendar format.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_DESP
columns.description: This column stores the drug description in free text.

columns.name: EXT_MED_REF_ID
columns.description: This column stores a reference identifier associated with each medication dispense.

columns.name: EXT_DRUD_ID_STR
columns.description: This column stores the identifier of the drug.

columns.name: EXT_MED_ERX_ID
columns.description: This column stores the matching medication ID for this drug.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_CODE_SYS
columns.description: This column stores the coding system used for the drug identifier.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_DISP_INST_DTTM
columns.description: This column stores the dispense instant.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_DISP_AMT
columns.description: This column stores the actual dispense amount of the drug.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_DISP_UNIT
columns.description: This column stores the drug dispense unit ID.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_UNIT_TXT
columns.description: This column stores the free text name of the dispense unit.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_DOSE_FORM
columns.description: This column stores the drug dosage form when dispensed.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_RX_NUM
columns.description: This column stores the prescription number of the dispense.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_DSPPROV_ID
columns.description: This column stores the dispensing provider ID.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_PROV_NAME
columns.description: The dispensing provider name for the external dispense.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_UNIT_STR
columns.description: This column stores the actual unit strength.

columns.name: EXT_DRUG_PHAR_PHON
columns.description: The pharmacy phone (or other contact) number associated with the external dispense.

columns.name: EXT_MED_DAY_SUPPLY
columns.description: This column stores the number of days the dispense is written for.

columns.name: EXT_MED_ORDPROV_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier of the ordering provider for this medication. This column is frequently used to link to the CLARITY_SER table.

columns.name: EXT_MED_ORD_PROVNAM
columns.description: The name of the ordering provider for this medication.

columns.name: EXT_MED_ENT_ORG_NAM
columns.description: This column stores the entering organization name of the dispense data.

columns.name: EXT_MED_ORD_ID
columns.description: This column stores the linked order ID for the corresponding order record in Epic, if one exists.

columns.name: EXT_MED_DISP_UNT_C_NAME
columns.description:
The mapped dose unit category ID for the external dispense.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes
